Durban - A man believed to be in his forties was shot dead on Sydney Road, near Blake Road, in Umbilo on Monday just after 8am. ALS Paramedics Medical Services spokesperson Garrith Jamieson said that when paramedics arrived at the scene they found various security companies in attendance. “A male, believed to be in his forties, was found lying next to his vehicle, with multiple gunshot wounds to his body,” said Jamieson. Jamieson said the man was assessed by Advanced Life Support paramedics. “However, he had sustained fatal injuries and there was nothing more paramedics could do for him and he was declared deceased on the scene.” He added that the SAPS were on the scene and would be investigating further. Provincial police spokesperson Constable Thenjiswa Ngcobo said Umbilo police are investigating a case of murder following a shooting incident that occurred on Monday, 23 January on Sydney Road.  “It is alleged that a 49-year-old man was at a parking lot outside his business premises when he was reportedly shot and killed unknown suspect, “ she said. In an unrelated incident, a man was stabbed to death in North Beach. Emer-G-Med spokesperson Kyle van Reenen said paramedics responded to a stabbing in Playfair Road on Monday just after 8.30am. “On arrival on the scene, a male, of approximately 30 years of age, was found to have sustained fatal stab injuries and was declared dead on arrival of paramedics,” he said. THE MERCURY